-- Deripaska Seeks to Build Grain Terminal at Russia Black Sea Port
-- B y   I l y a   K h r e n n i k o v
-- 2012-04-19T12:39:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-19/deripaska-seeks-to-build-grain-terminal-at-russia-black-sea-port.html
Russian billionaire Oleg Deripaska
plans to build a grain terminal in a new port area of Taman on
the  Black Sea , his holding company Basic Element said.  The company asked the Transportation Ministry to allow it
to build a terminal with capacity of 5 million metric tons a
year, it said today in a statement. Basic Element plans to
expand its agriculture operations through the project, as well
as a bid for state-run trader United Grain Co., it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
